\pagebreakNum

### Blue Dragonflight

*"I believe that you will find that my gift to you is not just a profound duty — which it is — but also a delight — which it is! Magic must be regulated, managed, and controlled. But it must also be appreciated and valued and not hoarded. Such is the contradiction you must deal with. May you be dutiful... and joyous both."*

<div style="text-align:Right">

— *Norgannon's blessing of the Blue Aspect*

</div>

Wreathed in swirls and eddies of snow-dusted air, blue dragons are covered in lustrous scales of azure blue and silvery white. The air around them is often cold. Magic is the domain of the blue dragonflight; they are charged with its use and care, for the power of magic is not to be taken lightly.

***Tending the Arcane.*** Led by the Aspect Malygos, and his mate Sindragosa, the blue dragonflight tended arcane magic for millennia. Native to the northern reaches that would one day become Northrend, they conducted many experiments. They even discovered other realms of existence, and spent much time watching over those who practiced magic.

***Betrayal and Death.*** During the War of the Ancients, the blue dragonflight was betrayed. When Deathwing used the Dragon Soul to turn on his allies, he all but wiped out the blue dragons. Malygos — overwhelmed by the loss of his mate, his friend Neltharion, and most of his kin — fell into a grief-stricken madness. The few blue dragons who remained, and a few remaining blue dragon eggs, were the flight's only hope for the future.

\columnbreak

<div style='margin-top:30px;'></div>

    ***The Nexus War.*** Some while after the defeat of Illidan, Malygos seemed to wake from his madness. He concluded that the mortal races had caused too much destruction with their reckless pursuit of power. He and the newly resurgent blue flight declared war on the Kirin Tor and began to siphon the magic of Azeroth, so that it could not be misused, but this had destructive effects on the world. Their efforts became so destructive that Alexstrsza and the other aspects saw no other course but to destroy Malygos.

***Spread to the Winds.*** No other dragonflight at that time had ever suffered the death of an Aspect. Leaderless, and without the guiding power of the Aspect in whom had been placed the power over arcane magic, the blue dragonflight was devastated once again. With the final destruction of Deathwing, this became a moot point, as the Aspects lost their immortality and much of their power.

Their numbers reduced yet again, lacking an Aspect, the blue dragonflight effectively dissolved. Blue dragons went their own way, each choosing their home and their goals as they saw fit. Most retained the dragonkin that were already in their service, but kept little contact with one another.

<img src='https://i.pinimg.com/originals/86/4e/b1/864eb1d19e86633f7ae53bede63f4159.jpg' style='position:absolute; bottom:-220px; right:0px; width:820px; transform:scalex(-1)' />
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/pZatMx5.png' style='position:absolute; top:-290px; left:-40px; height:1300px; transform:scale(-1) rotate(-9deg)' />

