>
> ***Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 12 (2d6 + 5) slashing damage.
>
> ***Tail.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 15ft., one target. *Hit:* 14 (2d8 + 5) bludgeoning damage.
>
> ***Frightful Presence.*** Each creature of the dragon's choice that is within 120 feet of the dragon and aware of it must succeed on a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw or become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's saving throw is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to the dragon's Frightful Presence for the next 24 hours.
>
> ***Breath Weapons (Recharge 5-6).*** The dragon uses one of the following breath weapons.
>
> **Spellfrost Breath.** The dragon exhales an icy blast in a 
<br/>    60-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a 
<br/>    DC 18 Dexterity saving throw, taking 31 (9d6) force 
<br/>    damage plus 17 (5d6) cold damage on a failed save, 
<br/>    or half as much damage on a successful one. 
> <br/> In addition, any creature damaged by the breath must 
<br/>    make a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw or lose spell 
<br/>    slots of combined level 2d4+1, starting with the 
<br/>    highest available level. The target regains any spell 
<br/>    slots lost in this way when they finish a short rest.
> **Repulsion Breath.** The dragon exhales repulsion energy 
<br/>    in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area must 
<br/>    make a DC 18 Strength saving throw or be pushed
<br/>    60 feet away from the dragon and they cannot cast
<br/>    any spells until the start of the dragon's next turn.
