>
> ***Tail.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +10 to hit, reach 15ft., one target. *Hit:* 16 (2d10 + 5) bludgeoning damage.
>
> ***Frightful Presence.*** Each creature of the dragon's choice that is within 120 feet of the dragon and aware of it must succeed on a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw or 
>
> become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can  repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's saving throw is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to the dragon's Frightful Presence for the next 24 hours.
>
> ***Breath Weapons (Recharge 5-6).*** The dragon uses one of the following breath weapons.
>
> **Searing Sand Breath.** The dragon exhales superheated 
<br/>    sand in a 60-foot cone. Each creature in that area 
<br/>    must make a DC 21 Dexterity saving throw, taking 
<br/>    49 (14d6) fire damage on a failed save and 
<br/>    becoming blinded until the end of the dragon's next 
<br/>    turn. On a success, a creature take half as much 
<br/>    damage to no other ill effect.
<br/> In addition, any creature damaged by the searing sand 
<br/>    breath must succeed a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw 
<br/>    or age 10% of its natural lifespan.
> <br/> **Slowing Breath.** The dragon exhales pure temporal 
<br/>    energy in a 60-foot cone. Each creature in that area 
<br/>    must succeed on a DC 18 Constitution saving throw. 
<br/>    On a failed save, the creature can't use reactions, its 
<br/>    speed is halved, and it can't make more than one 
<br/>    attack on its turn. In addition, the creature can use 
<br/>    either an action or a bonus action on its turn, but not 
<br/>    both. These effects last for 1 minute. The creature 
<br/>    can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its 
<br/>    turns, ending the effect on itself with a successful 
<br/>    save.
